article.headline: Robert Morris 89, Quinnipiac 77
article.story: CORAOPOLIS, Pa. (AP) -- Forward A.J. Jackson scored a career-high 39 points to lead Robert Morris to an 89-77 win over Quinnipiac on Sunday. Jackson was 14-of-21 shooting from the field and a perfect 8-for-8 at the free-throw line as Robert Morris (13-10, 9-5 in Northeast Conference) won its second consecutive game. Jackson also added 11 rebounds for his 13th double-double of the season and had a career-high four blocks. Derek Coleman with 14 points, Jeremy Chappell, 13, and Tony Lee, 11, were the other Colonials to get into double figures. The Colonials led 47-40 at the half. Quinnipiac (11-12, 6-8) took a 53-52 lead in the second half. But forward Colson Senat's three-pointer began an 11-2 run by the Colonials as they opened up a 63-55 lead with 10:09 left. The Bobcats were led by John Winchester, who scored 14 off the bench. He was joined in double figures by Dale Meinbresse, 13; Craig Benson, 12; and Karl Anderson and Victor Akinyanju, with 10 each.
